steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4rrph","text":"Dialyze purified LRRK2 RCKW into the final LRRK2 buffer (see Materials)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":17,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2f8fb","text":"Dilute the protein to the desired final concentration.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4acf9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b1e79","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"u95j","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"32i2p","text":"High concentrations favor dimers and trimers, while lower concentrations favor monomers. For the published trimer structure, a final concentration of 4 uM was used (see Deniston et al).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"29u53","text":"Glow discharge grids.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d67t0","text":"We used UltrAuFoil Holey Gold 1.2/1.3 300 mesh grids and glow discharged them at 20 mA for   in a K100 instrument.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":91,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1qjq2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":20,"guid":"20DEDA40636311EBB4106FFB24F69D20","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"78d1p","text":"(Optional) If adding inhibitors, add them after diluting to the final concentration and incubate on ice for   . If using Apo protein, then proceed immediately.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":108,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":3600,"guid":"BDF5F5D0636211EBB4106FFB24F69D20","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"975ln","text":"Apply protein to grids and plunge freeze.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7q3q7","text":"We used a Vitrobot (FEI) to blot away excess sample and plunge freeze","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
